@Flexina76 We will keep him indoors for the next 5+ days. Ideally for a week. He is an outdoor cat, and we can not make him not go outside after he has healed. He may have met a badger, or gotten stuck on something and ripped himself loose in panic. We do not know.

He will be on a pain killer for several days, will have an antibiotic twice per day for several days. Have to keep him indoors for a week. We'll see if he goes bananas and starts climbing the curtains by the end of day 5. Hoping to keep him inside until at least Monday morning.
In addition to that he has ripped out several claws on one of his back paws.  The vet cleaned up the claw stubs that are left and gave him an antibiotic shot plus a painkiller shot today. Tweet 2/3

Update on Leon: Content warning: Pet got hurt, medical treatment.
